# White Bean Pot Pies

## Ingredients
@ingredient 6 ramekins
@ingredient oil
@ingredient 1 onion
@ingredient salt
@ingredient pepper
@ingredient carrots
@ingredient flour
@ingredient white wine (optional)
@ingredient vegetable broth
@ingredient thyme
@ingredient white beans
@ingredient vegan butter (or coconut oil)
@ingredient ice cold water

## Instructions
@instruction Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (204 C) and arrange ramekins on a baking sheet.
@instruction Heat a large pot over medium heat. Add oil and onion, season with salt and pepper, and sauté until soft - about 4-5 minutes.
@instruction Add carrots, season with more salt and pepper, cook for 2-3 minutes, then add flour to coat.
@instruction Cook for 1 minute, slowly add white wine (if using) followed by vegetable broth, whisking continuously.
@instruction Add thyme and white beans. Bring mixture to a simmer, lower heat, and let cook for a few minutes.
@instruction Cover pot and remove from heat.

## Crust
@instruction In a mixing bowl, combine flour and salt. Add vegan butter (or coconut oil) and use a pastry cutter or fork until the mixture resembles wet sand.
@instruction Gradually add ice cold water (about 4-6 Tbsp) to form a dough.
@instruction Knead the dough gently in the bowl, gather scraps, and transfer to a floured surface. Form into a disc.

## Assembly
@instruction Roll out the dough to about 1/8-inch thick. Cut into squares slightly larger than ramekins.
@instruction Fill each ramekin with white bean mixture almost to the top. Place a pie crust square on each, pressing edges to seal.
@instruction Use a knife or toothpick to create small holes in the crust for steam escape.

## Baking
@instruction Bake pot pies at 400 degrees F (204 C) for 35-40 minutes, until filling is bubbly and crust is golden brown.
@instruction Let cool for 10 minutes before serving. Store leftovers covered in refrigerator up to 3-4 days or freeze up to 1 month.
